# PageSpeed Insights — implement fixes immediately

When the user sends a PageSpeed Insights report, Lighthouse screenshot, or Core Web Vitals analysis (any URL):

1. **Do not stop at analysis** — implement all reasonable code fixes in the same turn without asking permission first.
2. **Map audits to code** — e.g. LCP → hero image/fetch/skeleton, render-blocking → fonts/scripts, unused JS → lazy imports, images → dimensions/lazy/preload, CLS → width/height, a11y → labels/contrast where obvious.
3. **Prefer smallest high-impact diffs** — match existing patterns; avoid over-engineering.
4. **Update `seo/core_web_vitals_baseline.json`** when new scores are provided.
5. **Brief summary after** — what changed, expected metric impact, and what (if anything) cannot be fixed in code alone (e.g. external CDN images, CrUX “No Data”).
6. **Commit/push** only when the user explicitly asks — implement and commit locally if they ask to commit; never push to remote unless they say so.

Scope order: fix the **specific URL/page** audited first, then **shared bottlenecks** (`index.html` fonts, `Layout.tsx` third parties) if the audit calls them out.
